			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>Integrating Attribute Grammar and Functional Programming Language Features</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/TedKaminski.html">Ted Kaminski</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html">Eric Van Wyk</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_15">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_15</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagM">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> Attribute grammars are a meta-language; the paper focuses on integrating AG mechanisms with FP features.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is explicitly about integration of language mechanisms (AG + functional programming features).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The work supports implementation/tooling for such integrated language definitions (e.g., in compiler construction).
</li></ul></li></ul>
